transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I placed an order yesterday and I was trying to change the priority service on it for delivery.

Speaker 2: I wasn't able to do that.

Speaker 1: What was your last name?

Speaker 2: Witkowski, W-H-I-T.

Speaker 1: What?

Speaker 2: K-O-S-S-K-I.

Speaker 1: W-H-I-T-K-O-S-S-K-I?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: What's your zip code, sir?

Speaker 2: 3-0-0-2-8.

Speaker 1: David?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Perfect. It's at the pharmacy still.

Speaker 2: We do next day air for $38.

Speaker 1: It would go out today most likely and arrive tomorrow.

Speaker 2: We do two day air for $28 and priority mail for $15.

Speaker 1: Okay, so we don't know what time it would arrive tomorrow?

Speaker 2: No, I could not. I definitely couldn't give you that FedEx.

Speaker 1: They do what they will.

Speaker 2: Okay, so it would be FedEx then?

Speaker 1: If it was next day air or second day air.

Speaker 2: If it's priority mail, one to three days with USPS.

Speaker 1: Okay. I guess let's just keep it the way that it is.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem. You should still see that arrive by Friday, I'd say.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right, cool.

Speaker 2: All right. I appreciate you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.
